    "string": "We always determine the next type scale step based on the previous one. That’s why we have this math:\n\n\n\tX₂=X   ₁+{INT[(n-2)/4]+1}x2\n\n\n\tX  : step n type size     X   ₁ : step n-1 type size\n\nThe gap between two steps is always based on increments of 2. It is a non-linear arithmetic progression, providing a smaller interval (slope) for smaller type and a larger interval (slope) for large type, giving us a wide range of scales. It provides sensible value ands works well in a digital environment."
